If true, and [bottomNavigationBar] or [persistentFooterButtons] is specified, then the [body] extends to the bottom of the Scaffold, instead of only extending to the top of the [bottomNavigationBar] or the [persistentFooterButtons]. If true, a [MediaQuery] widget whose bottom padding matches the height of the [bottomNavigationBar] will be added above the scaffold's [body]. This property is often useful when the [bottomNavigationBar] has a non-rectangular shape, like [CircularNotchedRectangle], which adds a [FloatingActionButton] sized notch to the top edge of the bar. In this case specifying `extendBody: true` ensures that scaffold's body will be visible through the bottom navigation bar's notch. See also: [extendBodyBehindAppBar], which extends the height of the body to the top of the scaffold.
